The work of Professor Bavesh Kana and Dr Bhavna Gordhan has provided additional control to validate COVID-19 tests. JOHANNESBURG - Two scientists at the South African Medical Research Council have managed to harvest live coronavirus. The work of Professor Bavesh Kana and Dr Bhavna Gordhan has provided additional control to validate COVID-19 tests. READ: COVID-19: Survivors donate blood for testing Teams from Wits and Stellenbosch University, as well as the University of the Western Cape worked on the project. The scientists reconfigured their biosafety Level 3 labs from dealing with infectious bacteria to working with this new, highly infectious virus. This achievement is also expected to help with the development of new COVID-19 test kits. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Open configuration options